!&{template:traits} {{name=Grapple: @{selected|character_name} vs @{target|Grapple Target|character_name}}} {& define ([GrappleRoll] [[1d20+@{selected|athletics_bonus}]]) ([ContestedRoll] ?{@{target|Grapple Target|character_name} uses Athletics or Acrobatics|Athletics,[[1d20+@{target|Grapple Target|athletics_bonus}]]|Acrobatics,[[1d20+@{target|Grapple Target|acrobatics_bonus}]]})}({{source=Source:PHB p195}}{{description=When you want to grab a creature or wrestle with it, you can use the Attack action to make a special melee attack, a grapple. If you're able to make multiple attacks with the Attack action, this attack replaces one of them. The target of your grapple (@{target|Grapple Target|size}) must be no more than one size larger than you (@{selected|size}) , and it must be within your reach.%NEWLINE%GrappleRoll vs ContestedRoll{&if ([Grappled] GrappleRoll > ContestedRoll)} Success{&else} Failure{&end}}}{& if Grappled}%NEWLINE%!forselected+ cmaster --add,condition=grappled,duration=10 {&select @{target|Grapple Target|token_id}}{&end}{&simple}
